---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import "../styles/global.css";
---

<BaseLayout title="About — Pradeep" description="Engineering leader with a hands-on AI building practice. Currently targeting AI enablement leadership roles.">

  <section class="py-24">
    <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-6">

      <p class="font-mono text-accent-blue text-sm mb-3">~/about</p>

      <!-- Header: headshot + name -->
      <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row sm:items-center gap-6 mb-8">
        <img
          src="/profile-headshot.png"
          alt="Pradeep Kolakkampadath"
          class="w-28 h-28 rounded-full object-cover border border-border shadow-lg"
          width="112"
          height="112"
          loading="eager"
        />
        <div>
          <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold text-text-primary mb-1">Pradeep Kolakkampadath</h1>
          <p class="text-text-secondary text-base">Director of Software Engineering</p>
          <p class="text-text-muted text-sm mt-0.5">Greater St. Louis · AI Enablement · Agentic Systems</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Career snapshot stats -->
      <div class="animate-on-scroll flex flex-wrap gap-8 py-6 mb-10 border-y border-border">
        <div>
          <div class="text-2xl font-bold text-text-primary">20+</div>
          <div class="text-xs text-text-muted font-mono mt-0.5">years in software</div>
        </div>
        <div>
          <div class="text-2xl font-bold text-text-primary">50+</div>
          <div class="text-xs text-text-muted font-mono mt-0.5">person org led</div>
        </div>
        <div>
          <div class="text-2xl font-bold text-accent-blue">7</div>
          <div class="text-xs text-text-muted font-mono mt-0.5">AI projects live</div>
        </div>
        <div>
          <div class="text-2xl font-bold text-text-primary">2</div>
          <div class="text-xs text-text-muted font-mono mt-0.5">agentic platforms built</div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Professional Summary -->
      <div class="space-y-5 text-text-secondary leading-relaxed mb-16 animate-on-scroll" data-animate-delay="80">
        <p class="text-lg text-text-primary font-medium leading-relaxed">
          Most engineering leaders talk about AI. I build it. Then I use what I built to lead better.
        </p>
        <p>
          I run an engineering enablement organization at Evernorth Health Services. On nights and
          weekends, I ship multi-agent AI systems. Persistent operating systems, governance layers,
          QA agents, simulation platforms. Building is not a hobby. It is how I stay ahead of what
          is actually possible, and how I earn the right to lead AI adoption at scale.
        </p>
        <p>
          My next move is into AI enablement leadership. Roles where the question is how to make an
          entire engineering organization better with AI. Not whether to add a chatbot to the product.
        </p>
      </div>

      <!-- Strengths -->
      <div class="mb-16">
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-text-primary mb-6 flex items-center gap-2">
          <span class="font-mono text-accent-blue text-sm">01</span>
          Strengths
        </h2>
        <div class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
          {[
            { title: "AI-to-production translation", desc: "Turning AI capabilities into engineering practices that teams can actually adopt." },
            { title: "Agentic systems design", desc: "Multi-agent architectures with memory, routing, and durable state that work across sessions." },
            { title: "Product-minded leadership", desc: "Balancing what's technically interesting with what's worth building for real users." },
            { title: "Cross-functional communication", desc: "Bridging the gap between technical depth and business understanding." },
            { title: "Hands-on building", desc: "Not just directing. Building. Close to the craft by choice, not circumstance." },
            { title: "Team development", desc: "Growing engineers who think in systems and ship with confidence." },
          ].map((s, i) => (
            <div class="animate-on-scroll p-4 rounded-lg bg-surface-800/50 border border-border hover:border-accent-blue/20 transition-colors duration-200" data-animate-delay={i * 70}>
              <h3 class="font-medium text-text-primary text-sm mb-1">{s.title}</h3>
              <p class="text-text-secondary text-sm">{s.desc}</p>
            </div>
          ))}
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Working Style -->
      <div class="mb-16">
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-text-primary mb-6 flex items-center gap-2">
          <span class="font-mono text-accent-blue text-sm">02</span>
          How I Work
        </h2>
        <div class="space-y-4 text-text-secondary leading-relaxed">
          <p>
            I lead by building context and trust, not by prescription. Understanding the problem
            matters more than committing to a direction quickly. I want my teams to have the same
            depth of understanding I do. I prefer structured clarity over rigid process. Clear
            ownership. Explicit decisions. Room for people to do their best work.
          </p>
          <p>
            I am opinionated about quality but pragmatic about shipping. The best teams iterate
            fast with a clear sense of direction. I try to build that environment whether I am
            leading a team or building something myself.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- What I'm Looking For -->
      <div class="mb-16">
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-text-primary mb-6 flex items-center gap-2">
          <span class="font-mono text-accent-blue text-sm">03</span>
          What I'm Looking For
        </h2>
        <div class="space-y-4 text-text-secondary leading-relaxed">
          <p>
            I am targeting senior engineering leadership roles at the intersection of engineering
            and AI enablement. Positions where I can shape how engineering teams build with AI at
            both the strategic and tactical level. Specific titles vary by company. The substance
            is what matters.
          </p>
          <p>
            I am most interested in organizations that see AI as a capability to weave into
            engineering practice, not a product feature to ship. The question I want to work on
            is how to make an entire engineering org better with AI. Not whether to launch a chatbot.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Background -->
      <div class="mb-16">
        <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-text-primary mb-6 flex items-center gap-2">
          <span class="font-mono text-accent-blue text-sm">04</span>
          Background
        </h2>
        <div class="space-y-4 text-text-secondary leading-relaxed">
          <p>
            I've spent 20+ years in enterprise software delivery, moving from hands-on engineering
            into program and delivery leadership and now into platform-scale engineering enablement.
            Today I run an engineering enablement organization at Evernorth Health Services covering
            stability and resilience engineering, performance testing as an enterprise platform,
            test engineering and test data platforms, and delivery planning.
          </p>
          <p>
            Along the way I've led teams through large healthcare IT programs, modernized mainframe
            delivery with CI/CD patterns, partnered with security on enterprise remediation posture,
            and pushed AI from experimentation into governed, repeatable engineering workflows. The
            through line is turning capabilities into products teams actually use.
          </p>
          <p>
            In parallel I build AI systems. Multi-agent architectures, memory and routing design,
            durable state, and the operational patterns that make AI useful rather than impressive.
            The building directly informs the leadership. AI enablement that works on Tuesday
            morning, not just in a demo.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="mt-6">
          <a
            href="/resume"
            class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 text-accent-blue hover:text-accent-blue-hover text-sm font-medium"
          >
            Full resume and experience timeline
            <svg class="w-4 h-4" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24">
              <path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M13 7l5 5m0 0l-5 5m5-5H6" />
            </svg>
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- CTA -->
      <div class="pt-8 border-t border-border flex flex-wrap gap-4">
        <a
          href="/ask"
          class="px-6 py-3 bg-accent-blue hover:bg-accent-blue-hover text-white font-medium rounded-lg transition-colors"
        >
          Ask about my background
        </a>
        <a
          href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/valsa-kolakkampadath/"
          target="_blank"
          rel="noopener"
          class="px-6 py-3 bg-surface-800 hover:bg-surface-700 text-text-primary font-medium rounded-lg border border-border transition-colors"
        >
          LinkedIn
        </a>
      </div>

    </div>
  </section>

</BaseLayout>
